Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Jacqueline Danielle Duncan

records.addlTxt:
9:49 AM Defendant Jacqueline Danielle Duncan appeared by video.  Attorney Gabriel Andres Pollak in court for Jacqueline Danielle Duncan.  Prosecuting attorney Kevin Thomas Schmidt in court for the State of Wisconsin. Def appearing by Zoom with Court approval.  Def waives all in person hearing KIV.  Case on for Arraignment.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of information, def. waives reading.  Court informs def. of charges, possible penalties and rights.  NG plea entered to all counts.  Def to keep atty apprised of her location/progress.  Bond continues.
Status conference scheduled for December 8, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Status conference on December 8, 2022 at 09:00 am.

No use or possession of any illegal drugs, paraphernalia, or controlled substances without a valid prescription.
The defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety. Subject to random testing of breath, blood or urine bv any law
enforcement or corrections officer upon arrest or reasonable suspicion.
Amended 10/11/22 to a signature bond, as a bed at treatment has been secured. The defendant may be released to be immediately
transported directly to the treatment facility. If the defendant leaves the treatment facility for any reason, other
than graduation of the treatment program, she must be returned to the custody of Burnett County Jail and the cash
bond will go back into effect.

3:22 PM Defendant Jacqueline Danielle Duncan in court, in custody.  Attorney Gabriel Andres Pollak in court for Jacqueline Danielle Duncan.  Prosecuting attorney Kevin Thomas Schmidt in court for the State of Wisconsin. Waiver of Preliminary Hearing:  Court informs def of rights to PH; waived by def.  Court finds waiver of right to PH knowingly, freely, voluntarily made.  Court finds factual basis for bind over.  State files information mirroring complaint.  Separate arraignment date requested. Bond continues.
Arraignment scheduled for October 20, 2022 at 09:45 am.

No use or possession of any illegal drugs, paraphernalia, or controlled substances without a valid prescription. The defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety. Subject to random testing of breath, blood or urine by any law enforcement or corrections officer upon arrest or reasonable suspicion.  
Amended 9/21/22: Once a bed at treatment is secured, the defendant may be released to be immediately transported directly to the treatment facility.  If the defendant leaves the treatment facility for any reason, other than graduation of the treatment program, she must be returned to the custody of Burnett County Jail and the cash bond will go back into effect.

2:20 PM Defendant Jacqueline Danielle Duncan appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Gabriel Andres Pollak in court for Jacqueline Danielle Duncan.  Prosecuting attorney Kevin Thomas Schmidt in court for the State of Wisconsin. Def appears from Burnett County Jail.  Case on for an Initial Appearance.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of complaint, waives reading.  Court informs Defendant of charges, possible penalties and rights. NG plea entered to misdemeanor charge.  Atty Pollak requests to be heard on bond.  Court allows.  Atty Pollak argues for bond modification, notes def is arranging for programming.  State argues to wait to convert to signature bond until programming is arranged.  Court denies the bond modification at this time, adds condition- once treatment is secured, she may be released to a representative to transport her to the treatment facility.  If she leaves for any reason, she'll need to go back into custody and the cash bond will go back into effect.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 3, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
Preliminary hearing on October 3, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
